# Omninuera â€” Offer Letter for AI Intern

Date: [Start Date]

Dear [Candidate Full Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship/temporary engagement with Omninuera in the role of AI Intern. This letter outlines the principal terms of the internship. This is a draft and is subject to final approval following legal compliance review.

## 1. Role and Duration
- Role: AI Intern
- Duration: 3 months, commencing on [Start Date] (the "Term").

## 2. Reporting
- You will report to: [Reporting Manager].

## 3. Work Location and Hours
- Work location: Fully remote. Candidate is expected to be based in Bengaluru during the internship.
- Expected weekly commitment: 20 to 40 hours per week (flexible), to be agreed with your reporting manager. Remote work and flexible scheduling are permitted subject to team needs.

## 4. Nature of Engagement
- This engagement is an internship/temporary engagement. It does not constitute employment.
- You are not entitled to employee benefits, paid leave, provident fund, gratuity, or other statutory or contractual employee benefits unless explicitly stated in writing by Omninuera.

## 5. Stipend
- Stipend (not salary): INR 10,000 per month.
- Stipend payment schedule: Paid monthly via bank transfer to the account details provided by you. Please provide bank details to Omninuera for stipend payment: [Bank Account Details for Stipend].
- Payments will be processed on a monthly basis; standard processing timelines will apply.

## 6. Key Responsibilities
During the internship you will be expected to perform tasks including, but not limited to:
- Data preparation and cleaning for model development.
- Designing and running model experiments and prototypes.
- Model evaluation, analysis, and reporting of results.
- Documentation of experiments, code, and findings.
- Collaboration with the AI team and other stakeholders on assigned projects.

## 7. Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
- Confidentiality: You agree to keep confidential all non-public information of Omninuera that you learn or access during the internship. Confidentiality obligations survive the termination of the engagement.
- IP Assignment: You agree that all inventions, discoveries, developments, improvements, code, designs, data, reports, works of authorship and other intellectual property (collectively, the "Work Product") created by you, solely or jointly with others, in the course of or arising from the internship shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. To the extent permitted by applicable law, you hereby assign (or agree to assign) to Omninuera all right, title and interest in and to such Work Product and agree to execute documents as reasonably requested by Omninuera to effectuate such assignment.

## 8. Termination and Early Exit
- Either party may terminate this internship by providing at least one week (7 calendar days) prior written notice to the other party.
- Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause, including but not limited to breach of confidentiality, gross misconduct, theft, dishonesty, or unauthorized disclosure of company information.

## 9. Conditions
- This offer is subject to completion of any legal compliance review required by Omninuera.
- This offer may also be conditioned on satisfactory background verification where applicable. Any adverse result may lead to withdrawal or termination of the offer.

## 10. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
- This agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws applicable in Bengaluru, India. The courts in Bengaluru shall have exclusive jurisdiction over any disputes arising out of or in connection with this internship.

## 11. Acceptance
If you agree to the terms above, please sign and return a scanned or electronic copy of this letter to indicate your acceptance.

